-- Cowboys Defeat Giants 36-31 After Six Turnovers by New York
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2013-09-09T03:43:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-09/cowboys-defeat-giants-36-31-after-six-turnovers-by-new-york.html
The  Dallas Cowboys  held on for a
36-31 win over the New York Giants in the National Football
League regular season-opener for both teams, taking advantage of
six turnovers by their division rivals.  Brandon Carr had a 49-yard interception return for a
touchdown in the final two minutes to help clinch the victory
for the Cowboys at AT&T Stadium in Arlington, Texas.  Cowboys quarterback  Tony Romo  passed for 263 yards and
hooked up with tight end Jason Witten for a pair of touchdowns.
Barry Church scored on a 27-yard fumble return for Dallas, which
had 16 takeaways last season.  The Giants had turnovers on each of their first three
possessions, with two interceptions by Manning and a fumble by
 David Wilson . Manning finished with 450 passing yards and four
touchdowns, three to Victor Cruz.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
